article.headline: Canisius 87, Longwood 83
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Harold Washington scored a career-high 30 points, including eight straight in a key second-half run, and Alshwan Hymes added 24 as Canisius held off Longwood 87-83 Tuesday night. The Golden Griffins (1-1) led by 13 in the first half, but Longwood got within 44-43 at the break. Washington, who transferred from Cecil College, scored 21 points in the second half. After Canisius built a seven-point lead, the Lancers (1-2) pulled ahead 73-71 with 4:08 left on a jumper by Jeremiah Bowman, who scored a career-high 27 points. Washington then hit three straight jumpers and knocked down two free throws to put the Golden Griffins up by six with 1:36 to go. Longwood got within three with 18 seconds left, but Canisius went 4 for 4 from the free-throw line in the final 14 seconds. The Lancers' Antwan Carter added 21 points and 15 rebounds for his 29th career double-double.
